Ananya Garg-21BCE0518¶

1.Download the Employee Attrition Dataset

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/patelprashant/employee-attrition

2.Perfrom Data Preprocessing

3.Model Building using Logistic Regression and Decision Tree and Random Forest

4.Calculate Performance metrics

Data Collection.

o   Collect the dataset or Create the dataset

• Data Preprocessing.

o   Import the Libraries.
o   Importing the dataset.
o   Checking for Null Values.
o   Data Visualization.
o   Outlier Detection
o   Splitting Dependent and Independent variables
o-  Encoding
o   Feature Scaling.
o   Splitting Data into Train and Test.

• Model Building

o   Import the model building Libraries
o   Initializing the model
o   Training and testing the model
o   Evaluation of Model
o   Save the Model

In [39]:
Q1 = df['MonthlyIncome'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['MonthlyIncome'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
lower_whisker = Q1 -(1.5*IQR)
upper_whisker = Q3 + (1.5*IQR)
df['MonthlyIncome']=np.where(df['MonthlyIncome']>upper_whisker,upper_whisker,np.where(df['MonthlyIncome']<lower_whisker,lower_whisker,df['MonthlyIncome']))

Q1 = df['TrainingTimesLastYear'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['TrainingTimesLastYear'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
lower_whisker = Q1 -(1.5*IQR)
upper_whisker = Q3 + (1.5*IQR)
df['TrainingTimesLastYear']=np.where(df['TrainingTimesLastYear']>upper_whisker,upper_whisker,np.where(df['TrainingTimesLastYear']<lower_whisker,lower_whisker,df['TrainingTimesLastYear']))
